<p valign="top">namespace &minus; syntactic namespace
pseudo-device driver (type nam)</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top">The <i>nam</i>
pseudo-device driver provides mapping of OPEN(2) <br>
calls to underlying devices based on name syntax. <br>
The standard Xinu name for the namespace device is
<i>NAMESPACE</i>. <br>
The <i>nam</i> driver provides two operations as follows:
<br>
Open a device given its name and access mode (see ACCESS(2)
for <br>
an explanation of modes). <br>
Initialize the namespace by establishing a default
interpretation <br>
for names. <br>
Although system calls MOUNT(2), UNMOUNT(2), NAMMAP(2), and
<br>
NAMREPL(2) are intricate parts of the naming system, they
are <br>
not included in the driver simply because they do not fit
the <br>
read/write paradigm easily.</p>
